<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1034" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1034">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6354/186: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-09">December 9,
                                1939</date>.<lb/>[Received December 9—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2573. Embassy’s 2510, December 1, 5 p.m.<note n="94" xml:id="d1034fn94">Not printed; it had reported the quota for the first quarter of
                                1940 as established at 100 percent (800.6354/182).</note> Tin quota
                            for first quarter of 1940 raised to 120 percent of standard
                            tonnages.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>